The following CSS will fit the background image to the page dimensions and eliminate the letter boxing for all viewport ratios.<p><pre><code>   -webkit-background-size: cover;
   -moz-background-size: cover;
   -o-background-size: cover;
   background-size: cover;
</code></pre>
Before: <a href="http://bit.ly/NY7ZtE" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/NY7ZtE</a><p>After: <a href="http://bit.ly/POyEaA" rel="nofollow">http://bit.ly/POyEaA</a>

I once had a candidate claiming to be a senior PHP programmer solve fizzbuzz by doing something like this:
  if (strpos($i/3, ".") != null) 
or something like that.  I was sad.
